## 6.1 Overview

Remote MCP servers are internet-hosted, accessible from any MCP client. No local installation. Ideal for web-based AI apps, easy-to-use integrations, server-side processing/authentication.

Uses Claude.ai's Custom Connectors feature as example.

## 6.2 Custom Connectors

Bridge between Claude and remote MCP servers. Enable:
- Connect Claude to existing remote MCP servers
- Build custom remote MCP servers for proprietary tools

## 6.3 Connection Steps

### Step 1: Navigate to Connector Settings
Open Claude in browser → profile icon → "Settings" → "Connectors" section in sidebar.

### Step 2: Add a Custom Connector
Scroll to bottom → "Add custom connector" button.
Enter remote MCP server URL (with https:// and path). Click "Add".

### Step 3: Complete Authentication
Most servers require auth: OAuth, API keys, or username/password. Follow server prompts (may redirect to third-party auth provider or show form within Claude).

### Step 4: Access Resources and Prompts
Click paperclip icon in message input → attachment menu shows all resources/prompts from connected servers. Select items to include in conversation.

### Step 5: Configure Tool Permissions
Connectors settings → click connected server → enable/disable specific tools, set usage limits, configure security parameters.

## 6.4 Best Practices

- Verify authenticity before connecting
- Only connect to trusted sources
- Review permissions during authentication
- Organize connectors by purpose/project
- Remove unused connectors regularly

