## 7.1 Concept

Agent skills = portable instruction sets for AI coding assistants. Encode design decisions (deployment model, tool patterns, auth) so agents can interrogate use cases and scaffold servers.

Reference plugin: `mcp-server-dev` (`anthropics/claude-plugins-official`)

## 7.2 Three Composing Skills

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `build-mcp-server` | Entry point. Interrogates use case, picks deployment model + tool-design pattern, routes to specialized skills. |
| `build-mcp-app` | Adds interactive UI widgets (forms, pickers, dashboards) rendered inline in chat. |
| `build-mcpb` | Packages local stdio server with runtime as single `.mcpb` archive. No Node/Python install needed. |

Each skill ships `SKILL.md` + `references/` folder (auth flows, tool-design patterns, widget templates, manifest schemas).

Install in Claude Code:
```bash
/plugin marketplace add anthropics/claude-plugins-official
/plugin install mcp-server-dev
```

## 7.3 Discovery Phase (Questions Before Code)

- **What it connects to**: Cloud API, local process, filesystem, hardware
- **Who will use it**: Just you, your team, anyone
- **Action surface size**: Few ops vs large API wrapper
- **User interaction needs**: Plain text, structured input (elicitation), rich UI widgets
- **Upstream auth**: API keys, OAuth 2.0, none

## 7.4 Deployment Paths

### Path 1: Remote Streamable HTTP (DEFAULT)
For anything wrapping a cloud API. Zero install friction, one deployment serves all users, OAuth flows work properly (server handles redirects + token storage). Scaffolds for Cloudflare Workers, Express/FastMCP.

### Path 2: MCP Apps
Extends server with interactive widgets in chat (searchable pickers, charts, live dashboards). Handoff to `build-mcp-app` when elicitation's flat-form constraints don't fit.

### Path 3: MCP Bundles (MCPB)
Packages local server + runtime as single `.mcpb` archive. For servers that touch user's machine: reading local files, driving desktop apps, localhost services. Handoff to `build-mcpb`.

### Path 4: Local stdio
Prototyping only, with noted upgrade path to MCPB for distribution.

## 7.5 Next Steps After Scaffold
1. Iterate tool descriptions + error handling
2. Test with MCP Inspector
3. Wire into MCP client (local/remote config)
4. Publish to MCP Registry

